  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Temporary Accounts Assistant",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>The Accounts Assistant is responsible for day-to-day accounting and bookkeeping activities, including accounts payable, accounts receivable, billing, and monthly GST submission. The role ensures accurate financial records, timely reporting, and compliance with accounting and regulatory requirements. </p><p><br /><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Handle accounts payable and accounts receivable, including invoice processing, billing, and payment tracking.</li><li>Prepare and submit monthly GST returns accurately and on time.</li><li>Ensure all payment amounts tally with accounting records and supporting documents.</li><li>Assist in balancing accounts and preparing summaries of balances, cost information, and other financial reports as required.</li><li>Check and ensure accuracy of petty cash transactions and reconciliations.</li><li>File, organize, and maintain accounting and clerical records, including receipts, invoices, vouchers, expense claims, and related documentation.</li><li>Support general accounting and bookkeeping tasks and assist with ad-hoc finance-related duties.</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Qualifications & Experience</strong></p><p><strong>Education</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma in Accounting and Finance.</li></ul><p><strong>Experience</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum 2 years of experience in accounting, bookkeeping and GST reporting.</li></ul><p><strong>Skills & Competencies</strong>       </p><ul><li>Strong attention to detail and accuracy.</li><li>Good knowledge of accounting principles and bookkeeping practices.</li><li>Proficient in Microsoft Excel and accounting systems.</li><li>Well-organized and able to meet deadlines.</li><li>Ability to work independently and as part of a team.</li></ul><p><strong></strong><br /><strong>Other Information</strong><br />Working Hours: Mondays to Fridays, 8:30am - 6:00pm<br />Duration of Employment: 23 Feb 2026 – 31 Aug 2026</p>",
